# Create a program that will remove duplicates from a set

# Create a set
my_set = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9}

# Create a new set that will contain the unique elements from the original set
unique_set = set()

# Iterate through the original set and add the elements to the new set only if it is not already present
for element in my_set:
    if element not in unique_set:
        unique_set.add(element)

# Print the new set
print(unique_set)
